SIMPLE: pervade
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pervade
<hw>Per*vade"</hw> <pr>(p⟦etil⟧r*v⟦amac⟧d")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Pervaded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Pervading</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>pervadere</ets>, <ets>pervasum</ets>; <ets>per</ets> +
<ets>vadere</ets> to go, to walk. See <er>Per-</er>, and
<er>Wade</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To pass or flow through, as an
aperture, pore, or interstice; to permeate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That labyrinth is easily <qex>pervaded</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To pass or spread through the whole extent of; to be
diffused throughout.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A spirit of cabal, intrigue, and proselytism <qex>pervaded</qex>
all their thoughts, words, and actions.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>pervading</ent>⟦br⟧
